### Historical Context
Early computers used **punch cards** ğŸ·ï¸ to encode binary instructions. These cards had patterns of holes representing binary states, allowing machines to process information. Over time, vacuum tubes and transistors replaced punch cards, leading to faster and more reliable computing.

